    <title>Water contributor: Jerry Redfern</title>
    <description>Jerry Redfern is a senior fellow at the Schuster Institute for Investigative Journalism, covering environment, health and human rights, primarily in the developing world. He is coauthor, with Karen Coates, of the award-winning book “Eternal Harvest: The Legacy of American Bombs in Laos”. You can follow him on Instagram @jerryredfern, where you can see pictures of the Rio Grande near his home in New Mexico.
</description>
